items.title: Fed Chief Powell says stock prices appear 'fairly highly valued'
items.description: Powell on Tuesday noted that asset prices, a category that typically includes stocks and other risk instruments, are at elevated levels.

items.title: U.S. and global growth forecast lifted by OECD as economies surprise to the upside
items.description: The OECD noted that many economies have been more resilient than expected so far this year.

items.title: The Fed cut its interest rate, but long-term rates — including those on mortgages — went higher
items.description: Ten- and 30-year Treasury yields rose this week after the central bank cut its short-term interest rate.

items.title: Steve Bannon floats idea of Bessent running both Treasury and the Fed
items.description: White House confidante Steve Bannon has an unusual solution for who should take over as Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell next year.

items.title: Germany was billed as Europe's growth driver. Now economists are saying: Not so fast
items.description: Germany was a hub of excitement earlier this year amid high hopes of an economic rebound — domestically, and across Europe.
